<poem>
  <phead>
    <ptitle>Sonnet 57</ptitle>
    <author>
      <first-name>William</first-name>
      <last-name>Shakespeare</last-name>
    </author>
  </phead>
  <pbody>
    <stanza>
      <line>Being your slave what should I do but<phoneme category="a">tend</phoneme></line>
      <line>Upon the hours and times<phoneme category="b">desire</phoneme><phoneme category="b">desire</phoneme><phoneme category="b">desire</phoneme></line>
      <line>I have no precious time at all to<phoneme category="a">spend</phoneme></line>
      <line>Nor<phoneme category="b">require</phoneme><phoneme category="b">require</phoneme><phoneme category="b">require</phoneme><phoneme category="b">require</phoneme><phoneme category="b">require</phoneme><phoneme category="b">require</phoneme></line>
      <line>Nor dare I chide<phoneme category="c">hour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">hour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">hour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">hour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">hour</phoneme></line>
      <line>Whilst I my sovereign watch the clock for<phoneme category="d">you</phoneme></line>
      <line>Nor<phoneme category="c">sour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">sour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">sour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">sour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">sour</phoneme><phoneme category="c">sour</phoneme></line>
      <line>When you have bid your servant once<phoneme category="d">adieu</phoneme></line>
      <line>Nor dare I question with my jealous thought</line>
      <line>Where you may be or your affairs<phoneme category="f">suppose</phoneme></line>
      <line>But like a sad slave stay and think of nought</line>
      <line>Save where you are how happy you make<phoneme category="f">those</phoneme></line>
      <line>So true a fool is love that in your<phoneme category="g">will</phoneme></line>
      <line>Though you do any thing he thinks no<phoneme category="g">ill</phoneme></line>
    </stanza>
  </pbody>
</poem>